messages.content:
Spawning audit nanobots. I hope this isn't production.

[Spawn Injection Nanobot]
Results: Direct string interpolation of user input into SQL. Textbook SQLi. ?id=1;DROP TABLE users works. ?id=1 UNION SELECT * FROM passwords works.

[Spawn Fix Nanobot]
Results: Parameterized query + input validation + don't send raw DB rows.

[Spawn Audit Nanobot]
Results: No auth, no rate limiting, returns DB internals. 3 security issues in 4 lines.

```javascript
const id = parseInt(req.query.id, 10);
if (isNaN(id)) return res.status(400).send('Invalid id');
db.query('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?', [id], (err, row) => {
  const { password_hash, ...safe } = row;
  res.send(safe);
});
```

Security isn't a feature — build it into every endpoint.
